      "Upload a CSV or Excel file and get a fully functional REST API instantly. Django parses the file with pandas, infers column types at a 90% match threshold, creates a SQLite table dynamically at runtime using Python's type() constructor, and registers DRF ViewSets and URL routes without a server restart. Full CRUD, API key auth, rate limiting, and OpenAPI/Swagger docs included.",
    tech: ['Django 4.2', 'Django REST Framework', 'React 19', 'TypeScript', 'Vite 7', 'Tailwind CSS 4', 'pandas', 'drf-spectacular (OpenAPI 3.0)'],
    github: 'https://github.com/Tyler-Irving/file-to-api',
    stats: [
      { label: 'Upload → Live API', value: '<5s' },
      { label: 'Rate Limit (reads)', value: '1k/hr' },
      { label: 'Max Upload', value: '10 MB' },
    ],
    decisions: [
      "Dynamic model generation at runtime via Python's type() constructor — no code generation, no server restart on upload",
      'Runtime DRF router registration — ViewSets and URL routes injected into live URL conf without touching urls.py',
      'SHA-256 + salt API key hashing with 8-char plaintext prefix for O(1) lookup — format: fta_{prefix}_{secret}',
